article.headline: Robert Morris 68, Quinnipiac 68
article.story: CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- Chaz McCrommon blocked Rashaun Banjo's effort at a game-tying jump shot with 10 seconds left and Quinnipiac never got another shot off as they fell 68-66 to Robert Morris Thursday night. McCrommon played 40 minutes for Robert Morris (13-13, 10-7 Northeast Conference) and had 18 points. Banjo led all scorers with 22 points for Quinnipiac (8-19, 4-12). Robert Morris led 40-38 at the half. After McCrommon's game-saving block, Kason Mims got the ball back for Quinnipiac but turned it over to Aaron Thomas, who was then fouled by Banjo. Thomas missed the first half of a one-and-one, but the clock ran out before Quinnipiac could get a shot off after the missed free throw. Mims finished with 18 points for Quinnipiac. Maurice Carter led Robert Morris with 21 points, while Thomas added 12 and Mark Anderson 10.
